: SCTID\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: AAO part_of NCBITaxon:8292\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: DHBA part_of NCBITaxon:9606\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: EHDAA2 part_of NCBITaxon:9606\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: EMAPA part_of NCBITaxon:10090\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: FBdv part_of NCBITaxon:7227\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: FMA part_of NCBITaxon:9606\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: HAO part_of NCBITaxon:7399\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: HBA part_of NCBITaxon:9606\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: KUPO part_of NCBITaxon:9606\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: MA part_of NCBITaxon:10090\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: MFO part_of NCBITaxon:8089\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: PBA part_of NCBITaxon:9443\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: SPD part_of NCBITaxon:6893\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: TADS part_of NCBITaxon:6939\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: TAO part_of NCBITaxon:32443\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: TGMA part_of NCBITaxon:44484\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: WBbt part_of NCBITaxon:6237\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: WBls part_of NCBITaxon:6237\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: XAO part_of NCBITaxon:8353\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: ZFA part_of NCBITaxon:7954\ntreat-xrefs-as-reverse-genus-differentia: ZFS part_of NCBITaxon:7954\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0002740\nname: posterior cingulate gyrus\ndef: \"The posterior cingulate cortex is the backmost part of the cingulate cortex, lying behind the anterior cingulate cortex. This is the upper part of the 'limbic lobe'. The cingulate cortex is made up of an area around the midline of the brain. Surrounding areas include the retrosplenial cortex and the precuneus. Cytoarchitectonically posterior cingulate cortex is associated with Brodmann areas 23 and 31. [WP,unvetted].\" [Wikipedia:Posterior_cingulate_gyrus]\nsubset: uberon_slim\nsynonym: \"cGp\" BROAD OMO:0003000 [FMA:61924, FMA:CMA]\nsynonym: \"gyrus cinguli posterior\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [NeuroNames:162]\nsynonym: \"gyrus limbicus posterior\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [NeuroNames:162]\nsynonym: \"PCgG\" BROAD OMO:0003000 [BIRNLEX:1546, NIFSTD:NeuroNames_abbrevSource]\nsynonym: \"posterior cingulate\" RELATED [NeuroNames:162]\nxref: BAMS:PCgG\nxref: BIRNLEX:1546\nxref: FMA:61924\nxref: neuronames:162 {source=\"BIRNLEX:1546\"}\nxref: UMLS:C0175191 {source=\"BIRNLEX:1546\"}\nxref: Wikipedia:Posterior_cingulate_gyrus\nis_a: UBERON:0000200 ! gyrus\ndisjoint_from: UBERON:0002756 {source=\"lexical\"} ! anterior cingulate gyrus\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002967 ! cingulate gyrus\nproperty_value: depiction \"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/fe/Gray727.svg\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0002756\nname: anterior cingulate gyrus\nsubset: uberon_slim\nsynonym: \"anterior cingulate\" RELATED [NeuroNames:161]\nsynonym: \"cGa\" BROAD OMO:0003000 [FMA:61916, FMA:CMA]\nsynonym: \"cingulate gyrus, anterior division\" BROAD [http://orcid.org/0000-0001-6755-0259]\nsynonym: \"cortex cingularis anterior\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [NeuroNames:161]\nsynonym: \"gyrus cinguli anterior\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [NeuroNames:161]\nsynonym: \"gyrus limbicus anterior\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [NeuroNames:161]\nxref: BAMS:ACgG\nxref: BIRNLEX:1603\nxref: FMA:61916\nxref: neuronames:161 {source=\"BIRNLEX:1603\"}\nxref: UMLS:C0175190 {source=\"BIRNLEX:1603\"}\nis_a: UBERON:0000200 ! gyrus\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002967 ! cingulate gyrus\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0009835 ! anterior cingulate cortex\nproperty_value: depiction \"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/22/Gray727_anterior_cingulate_cortex.png\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0006101\nname: Brodmann (1909) area 24\ndef: \"Missing definition for term UBERON:0006101. Please replace it using linked reference.\" [BIRNLEX:1755]\nsynonym: \"agranular cingulate area\" RELATED [NeuroNames:1007]\nsynonym: \"anterior cingulate area\" RELATED [NeuroNames:1007]\nsynonym: \"area 24 of Brodmann\" EXACT [FMA:68621]\nsynonym: \"area 24 of Brodmann-1905 (guenon)\" RELATED [NeuroNames:1007]\nsynonym: \"area 24 of Brodmann-1909\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1755]\nsynonym: \"area cingularis anterior ventralis\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1755]\nsynonym: \"B09-24\" BROAD OMO:0003000 [BIRNLEX:1755, NIFSTD:SumsDB_abbrevSource]\nsynonym: \"B09-24\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1755]\nsynonym: \"BA24\" EXACT OMO:0003000 []\nsynonym: \"Brodmann (1909) area 24\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1755]\nsynonym: \"Brodmann area 24\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1755]\nsynonym: \"brodmann's area 24\" RELATED [NeuroNames:1007]\nsynonym: \"gyrus limbicus anterior\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [NeuroNames:1007]\nsynonym: \"ventral anterior cingulate\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1755]\nxref: BAMS:ACA\nxref: BIRNLEX:1755\nxref: FMA:68621\nxref: MBA:31\nxref: neuronames:1007 {source=\"BIRNLEX:1755\"}\nxref: UMLS:C1272542 {source=\"BIRNLEX:1755\"}\nxref: Wikipedia:Brodmann_area_24\nis_a: UBERON:0013529 {source=\"FMA\"} ! Brodmann area\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0009835 {source=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3308-6245\"} ! anterior cingulate cortex\nproperty_value: seeAlso \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1161\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0009835\nname: anterior cingulate cortex\ndef: \"The frontal part of the cingulate cortex that resembles a collar form around the corpus callosum. It includes both the ventral and dorsal areas of the cingulate cortex. Wikipedia:File:Gray727.svg.\" [BIRNLEX:936]\nsynonym: \"ACC\" RELATED OMO:0003000 [BTO:0004249]\nxref: BIRNLEX:936\nxref: BTO:0004249\nxref: FMA:271599\nxref: Wikipedia:Anterior_cingulate_cortex\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 ! regional part of brain\ndisjoint_from: UBERON:0022353 {source=\"lexical\"} ! posterior cingulate cortex\nrelationship: capable_of_part_of GO:0002027 {source=\"Wikipedia\"} ! regulation of heart rate\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0003027 {source=\"BTO\"} ! cingulate cortex\nproperty_value: depiction \"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/22/Gray727_anterior_cingulate_cortex.png\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0022438\nname: rostral anterior cingulate cortex\ndef: \"Component of the cingulate cortex. The rostral boundary was the first appearance of the cingulate sulcus (inferior to the superior frontal sulcus) whereas the caudal boundary was the first appearance of the genu of the corpus callosum. The medial boundary was the medial aspect of the cortex. The supero-lateral boundary was the superior frontal gyrus whereas the infero-lateral boundary was defined as the medial division of the orbitofrontal gyrus (Christine Fennema-Notestine).\" [BIRNLEX:975]\nsynonym: \"rostral anterior cingulate cortex\" EXACT HUMAN_PREFERRED [BIRNLEX:975]\nxref: BIRNLEX:975\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0009835 {source=\"NIFSTD\"} ! anterior cingulate cortex\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0027076\nname: obsolete regional part of Anterior cingulate cortex\nsynonym: \"regional part of anterior cingulate cortex\" EXACT HUMAN_PREFERRED [BIRNLEX:960]\nis_obsolete: true\nconsider: BIRNLEX:960\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0028715\nname: caudal anterior cingulate cortex\ndef: \"Component of the cingulate cortex. The rostral boundary was the first appearance of the genu of the corpus callosum whereas the caudal boundary was established as the first appearance of the mammillary bodies. The medial boundary was the medial aspect of the cortex. The supero-lateral boundary was the superior frontal gyrus whereas the infero-lateral boundary was the corpus callosum (Christine Fennema-Notestine).\" [BIRNLEX:967]\nsynonym: \"caudal anterior cingulate cortex\" EXACT HUMAN_PREFERRED [BIRNLEX:967]\nxref: BIRNLEX:967\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0009835 ! anterior cingulate cortex\n\n","exit":0,"description":"Shows anterior cingulate cortex terms","truncated":false},"title":"Shows anterior cingulate cortex terms","time":{"start":1778378536528,"end":1778378536530}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f014bd7e74996470169ffe72857c48196a50d37a8091b1bce"}},"id":"prt_e0f9ef60f001ej1sb9j5WDdbeN","sessionID":"ses_1f061be8dffexBOArtmOnExSA3","messageID":"msg_e0f9ed8d1001gr9UuV5CXRLzTI"}}
