{"type":"text","timestamp":1778378647646,"sessionID":"ses_1f061be8dffexBOArtmOnExSA3","part":{"id":"prt_e0fa09fba001Y3Seb4vtCMpK8U","messageID":"msg_e0fa06e14001Rw8SLXjVPiYqrb","sessionID":"ses_1f061be8dffexBOArtmOnExSA3","type":"text","text":"I found PMID:28317116, “Anatomical segmentation of the human medial prefrontal cortex,” which directly supports mPFC as an anatomically segmented medial prefrontal region and identifies human mPFC subareas including areas 24, 25, and 32. I’m keeping the ontology axioms conservative: `regional part of brain` plus `part_of prefrontal cortex`, with the Brodmann details in the text definition rather than hard-coding a full cross-species `has_part` composition.","time":{"start":1778378645434,"end":1778378647644},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_08b969a886acfce90169ffe7956ae4819d8e204c30503e2e93","phase":"commentary"}}}}
